hopobject.body: I'm sorry, he's pharmore drugs jobs These ingredients are especially common in Europe, so you're even more likely to encounter them in imported packaged foods. Essentially, they are highly processed carbohydrates derived from wheat – meaning that the protein (gluten) portion should have been fully separated from it. The operative phrase is: "should have been." It usually is, and as a result, it's not uncommon to see products that contain these ingredients bearing a "gluten-free" claim. But serendipitous removal of most gluten isn't good enough by the FDA's rule; these wheat-based products must be deliberately processed to ensure the raw ingredient is thoroughly decontaminated from gluten.
